HEADWORD: Spoutfish
<hw>Spout"fish`</hw> <pr>(-f⟦icr⟧sh`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A marine animal that spouts water; -- applied
especially to certain bivalve mollusks, like the long clams
(<gen>Mya</gen>), which spout, or squirt out, water when retiring into
their holes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spoutless</ent>⟦br⟧
